\text{P(Abe wins) = P(Abe wins in the first roll) + P(Abe wins in the second roll) + } \dots
=\frac{2}{6}+\frac{1}{6}\frac{2}{6} + \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^2 \frac{2}{6} + \dots
=\frac{1}{3}\left(1+\frac{1}{6}+\left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^2 + \dots\right)
=\frac{1}{3}\frac{1}{1-\frac{1}{6}}
=\frac{2}{5}
